<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="256" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,690,1869]" pageId="4" pageNumber="256">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,870,896]" pageId="4" pageNumber="256">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Recognized among species of 
<taxonomicName box="[672,784,871,897]" class="Insecta" family="Schizopteridae" genus="Corixidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="256" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[672,784,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="256">Corixidea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the uniformly dark coloration, macropterous forewing without a pale band (
<figureCitation box="[394,493,907,933]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1952,1976]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,597,1929]" captionTargetId="figure-217@3.[151,1436,597,1929]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Habitus of Corixidea graziae sp. nov., Corixidea quilombola sp. nov., and Schizoptera (Cantharocoris) savannensis sp. nov. in dorsal, ventral, and lateral views. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4691704" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4691704/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="256">Figure 2</figureCitation>
), mediotergite 8 asymmetrical, with process insertion on the left side (
<figureCitation box="[1303,1422,907,933]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1822,1846]" captionTargetBox="[169,1429,604,1786]" captionTargetId="figure-109@5.[151,1436,597,1798]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Male genitalic features. A. Corixidea graziae sp. nov. B. Corixidea quilombola sp. nov. C–D. Schizoptera (Cantharocoris) savannensis sp. nov. C. Ventral view of abdominal apex; black arrow points to posterior process of sternum 6 and white arrow points to lateral process of subgenital plate. D. Dorsal view. Abbreviations: lca = left conjunctival appendage, lp = left paramere, rca = right conjunctival appendage, rp = right paramere, st6 = sternum 6, st7 = sternum 7 (subgenital plate), mt8 = mediotergite 8, mt8p = mediotergite 8 process, py = pygophore, v = vesica. Scale bars: A–B = 0.1 mm, B–C = 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4691708" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4691708/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="256">Figure 3B</figureCitation>
), process of mediotergite 8 anteriorly directed, composed of an elongate projection mostly covered with many small pointed projections and a widened triangular plate-like base (
<figureCitation box="[852,971,979,1005]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1822,1846]" captionTargetBox="[169,1429,604,1786]" captionTargetId="figure-109@5.[151,1436,597,1798]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Male genitalic features. A. Corixidea graziae sp. nov. B. Corixidea quilombola sp. nov. C–D. Schizoptera (Cantharocoris) savannensis sp. nov. C. Ventral view of abdominal apex; black arrow points to posterior process of sternum 6 and white arrow points to lateral process of subgenital plate. D. Dorsal view. Abbreviations: lca = left conjunctival appendage, lp = left paramere, rca = right conjunctival appendage, rp = right paramere, st6 = sternum 6, st7 = sternum 7 (subgenital plate), mt8 = mediotergite 8, mt8p = mediotergite 8 process, py = pygophore, v = vesica. Scale bars: A–B = 0.1 mm, B–C = 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4691708" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4691708/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="256">Figure 3B</figureCitation>
); right paramere elongate and narrowed, strongly arched, bearing a small claw-like projection and a cluster of four small fine setae on the tip (
<figureCitation box="[1282,1400,1015,1041]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1822,1846]" captionTargetBox="[169,1429,604,1786]" captionTargetId="figure-109@5.[151,1436,597,1798]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Male genitalic features. A. Corixidea graziae sp. nov. B. Corixidea quilombola sp. nov. C–D. Schizoptera (Cantharocoris) savannensis sp. nov. C. Ventral view of abdominal apex; black arrow points to posterior process of sternum 6 and white arrow points to lateral process of subgenital plate. D. Dorsal view. Abbreviations: lca = left conjunctival appendage, lp = left paramere, rca = right conjunctival appendage, rp = right paramere, st6 = sternum 6, st7 = sternum 7 (subgenital plate), mt8 = mediotergite 8, mt8p = mediotergite 8 process, py = pygophore, v = vesica. Scale bars: A–B = 0.1 mm, B–C = 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4691708" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4691708/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="256">Figure 3B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="256" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,690,1869]" pageId="4" pageNumber="256">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,414,1050,1077]" pageId="4" pageNumber="256">Description. Male</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[429,528,1051,1077]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1952,1976]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,597,1929]" captionTargetId="figure-217@3.[151,1436,597,1929]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Habitus of Corixidea graziae sp. nov., Corixidea quilombola sp. nov., and Schizoptera (Cantharocoris) savannensis sp. nov. in dorsal, ventral, and lateral views. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4691704" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4691704/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="256">Figure 2</figureCitation>
): macropterous, body elongate-oval. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[949,1087,1050,1076]" pageId="4" pageNumber="256">Coloration:</emphasis>
general coloration dark brown and costal area of the forewing dark brown to black, remainder of wing dark brown, antenna and legs uniformly yellow, abdomen dark brown. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[498,765,1122,1149]" pageId="4" pageNumber="256">Surface and vestiture:</emphasis>
head, pronotum, and wing veins with medium-length light brown setae, abdomen densely covered with elongate, light brown setae. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1006,1213,1158,1185]" pageId="4" pageNumber="256">Structure: Head:</emphasis>
rounded in ventral view, width of eye about 1/3 width of synthlipsis, ocellus about the same size to one ommatidium, placed close to the lateral margin of compound eye. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[619,717,1231,1257]" pageId="4" pageNumber="256">Thorax:</emphasis>
pronotum trapezoidal, with posterior margin slightly concave medially, scutellum triangular, with a rounded tip, hind coxa with well-developed adhesive pad, tarsal formula 3- 3-3. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[204,330,1302,1328]" pageId="4" pageNumber="256">Abdomen:</emphasis>
with six visible sterna corresponding to segments 2+3, 4, 5, 6, 7, and pygophore. Mediotergite 8 asymmetrical, with process insertion on the left side. Process of mediotergite 8 anteriorly directed, composed of an elongate projection mostly covered with many small pointed projections and a widened triangular plate-like base. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,261,1410,1436]" pageId="4" pageNumber="256">Genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[280,402,1411,1437]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1822,1846]" captionTargetBox="[169,1429,604,1786]" captionTargetId="figure-109@5.[151,1436,597,1798]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Male genitalic features. A. Corixidea graziae sp. nov. B. Corixidea quilombola sp. nov. C–D. Schizoptera (Cantharocoris) savannensis sp. nov. C. Ventral view of abdominal apex; black arrow points to posterior process of sternum 6 and white arrow points to lateral process of subgenital plate. D. Dorsal view. Abbreviations: lca = left conjunctival appendage, lp = left paramere, rca = right conjunctival appendage, rp = right paramere, st6 = sternum 6, st7 = sternum 7 (subgenital plate), mt8 = mediotergite 8, mt8p = mediotergite 8 process, py = pygophore, v = vesica. Scale bars: A–B = 0.1 mm, B–C = 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4691708" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4691708/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="256">Figure 3B</figureCitation>
): Pygophore asymmetrical and almost triangular. Left paramere triangular and plate-like. Right paramere elongate and narrowed, strongly arched, bearing a small claw-like projection and a cluster of four small fine setae on the tip. Aedeagus long and thin, without processes. Anophoric process absent.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="256" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,690,1869]" pageId="4" pageNumber="256">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1519,1545]" pageId="4" pageNumber="256">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet quilombola refers to people who inhabit quilombo communities. Quilombos are Black rural communities made by the descendants of African-American slaves, who live, in their majority, from subsistence agriculture. They are founded mainly during colonial Portuguese rule in 
<collectingCountry box="[1137,1205,1591,1617]" name="Brazil" pageId="4" pageNumber="256">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(between 1530 and 1815) by escaped slaves. This species’ name is indeclinable.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
