</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="256" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,690,1869]" pageId="4" pageNumber="256">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1699,1725]" pageId="4" pageNumber="256">Remarks.</emphasis>
This new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Emsley, 1969" authorityName="Emsley" authorityYear="1969" box="[681,1110,1699,1725]" class="Insecta" family="Schizopteridae" genus="Corixidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="256" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="underwoodii">
<emphasis box="[681,945,1699,1725]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="256">Corixidea underwoodii</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Emsley, M. G." box="[955,1110,1699,1725]" pageId="4" pageNumber="256" pagination="1 - 154" refId="ref4419" refString="Emsley, M. G. (1969) The Schizopteridae (Hemiptera: Heteroptera) with the descriptions of new species from Trinidad. Memoirs of the American Entomological Society, 25, 1 - 154." type="journal article" year="1969">Emsley, 1969</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1184,1405,1699,1725]" name="Trinidad and Tobago" pageId="4" pageNumber="256">Trinidad &amp; Tobago</collectingCountry>
in having a very long and anteriorly directed process of mediotergite 8. However, in 
<taxonomicName authority="Albuquerque &amp; De-Souza &amp; Favacho &amp; Carvalho-Filho, 2021" authorityName="Albuquerque &amp; De-Souza &amp; Favacho &amp; Carvalho-Filho" authorityYear="2021" box="[1117,1281,1735,1761]" class="Insecta" family="Schizopteridae" genus="Corixidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="256" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quilombola" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1117,1281,1735,1761]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="256">C. quilombola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1291,1384,1735,1761]" pageId="4" pageNumber="256">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1291,1384,1735,1761]" pageId="4" pageNumber="256" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, the process of mediotergite 8 is mostly covered with many small pointed projections, while in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Emsley" authorityYear="1969" box="[1172,1347,1771,1797]" class="Insecta" family="Schizopteridae" genus="Corixidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="256" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="underwoodii">
<emphasis box="[1172,1347,1771,1797]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="256">C. underwoodii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it bears tiny setulae on the tip and basally. These species belong to one of the two subgroups of the 
<emphasis box="[1200,1273,1807,1832]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="256">crassa</emphasis>
species group because they have an anteriorly directed process of tergum 8 (
<bibRefCitation author="Knyshov, A. &amp; Hoey-Chamberlain, R. &amp; Weirauch, C." box="[844,1078,1843,1869]" pageId="4" pageNumber="256" pagination="985 - 995" refId="ref4752" refString="Knyshov, A., Hoey-Chamberlain, R. &amp; Weirauch, C. (2019) Hybrid enrichment of poorly preserved museum specimens refines homology hypotheses in a group of minute litter bugs (Hemiptera: Dipsocoromorpha: Schizopteridae). Systematic Entomology, 44 (4), 985 - 995. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / syen. 12368" type="journal article" year="2019">
Knyshov 
<emphasis box="[954,1010,1843,1869]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="256">et al.</emphasis>
2019
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
